column15: MUMM (follow-up activities at sea) covers a large area of research within the Belgian Part of The North Sea (BPNS). For the follow-up of environmental impacts of offshore windfarms in the BPNS this is mainly concentrated within the eastern zone (where the concession zones are situated). The Marine Biology department of the UGhent has been responsible for the monitoring of soft-sediment macrobenthos within two offshore windfarms (C-Power, Belwind) within the BPNS. Before installation, T0 baseline data was collected and since 2015, a yearly large-scale monitoring (macrobenthos sampling) is conducted within both windfarms and at reference sites.
